body: @chr0n1x, what does 'go version' print? And 'go tool -n cover'? It sounds like you are not using a binary distribution, and that you built from old sources from before we moved cmd/cover into the main tree. It doesn't sound like Go 1.7. In any event, that seems unrelated to this issue, so please open a separate issue or mail golang-nuts to continue debugging that problem.
